The course deals with the historical development of law, its place in the social system and within the regulations of social relations, the basic concepts of the legal culture of continental Europe, the system of law and its realization. The course gives an overview of the basic concepts of labor law and civil service.
Parliament. The Government of the Republic. The President of the Republic. Authorities of the executive power. Judicial system. Local government. Chancellor of Justice.  Basic concepts of public administration. Sources and basic concepts of administrative law. Principles of administrative management.
A short historical overview of the formation of the European Union and Estonia's accession to the EU. The main decision-making processes in the EU and Estonia's participation in these. The principles of the creation and spending of the budget of the European Union. The main policies and their impact on EU developments, including the impact on Estonia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1. The aim of the course is to provide an understanding of the position and meaning of law and public administration within the regulations of social relations, and the ability to understand the system and basic terms of law and public administration.  2. After completing the course the student will be able to implement the knowledge of the main processes and policies of the European Union and combine these with the knowledge acquired in other courses.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) understands, analyses and uses the basic concepts of law and public administration, competences and organization of constitutional institutions; 2) understands, analyses and uses the correct terminology of administrative management; 3) understands, analyses and uses legal knowledge appropriate to case resolution; 4) understands, analyses and uses European Union policies and operating processes, and Estonia's role in these.
